A memorial service was held on Friday for the 14 pupils who lost their lives in the Kakamega Primary School tragedy. The service was held at Bukhungu Stadium. Government officials present included Education CS George Magoha and PS Belio Kipsang. Knut secretary Wilson Sossion was also present and he accused the ministry of negligence. Sossion also dismissed the autopsy released on Thursday, which showed students' died of suffocation. "These students' death was caused by congestion out of the negligenceÂ of the Ministry of Education of not guiding the school property," Sossion said.